I basically spammed her for a good minute or two she didn't respond so I watched a vid about it and it said one of the people who died was a 14 year old girl... she's a 14 year old girl at this point my sister and mum thought she was ok but I didn't know what to believe and then I got my answer............
she was alive and she called me and we talked a bit the 3rd akt was obviously a 10 there was a 4th akt but I'm not going to talk about it but it wasn't any worse then the 13th anyway so there's my mile long comment about "That Week" it was easily the worst time of my life and now I'm over it

snippet.textDisplay:
The worst emotional pain I have experienced was a couple months ago when the love of my life, a Golden Retriever Labrador mix, Shadow passed away. It was May 10th of this year, at 2:30 PM that we had to drive to the vet to put her down. She’d been fighting liver disease for over a year, and was a little over 14 years old.

It’s been a couple months but this was the first year I spent Halloween, Thanksgiving and Christmas without her. And tomorrow would have been her 15th birthday if she was still with us. It hurts like he’ll knowing I’ll never get to see her again but I’ve gotten to the point where I can talk about it without crying.

In honor of her death a friend of mine made me two aesthetics of her and a story from her point of view for me for Christmas. Luckily I have two lovely puppies that she took care of in her last year of life that I watch over now. They share so much of Shadow’s attitude and every time I see them I just light up. Shadow loved everyone, and everything underneath the sun. She loved watching your videos with me. We’d always fall asleep close to each other when watching you videos. She would also (when she could jump) come into me and my siblings rooms at night and lay on our beds to make sure we were safe. She loved us so so dearly, and I hope we gave her the best life she could have ever hoped for.

snippet.textDisplay: I like the family death serious talk. My grandma died a few months ago, and since she always lived thousands of miles away from me and we never really talked, I almost felt nothing when I heard the news. It took me a full month to comprehend what was going on. I finally felt the weight when her Celebration of Life occurred a month after and I heard my dad break down in tears in his speech. That was the first time I cried and I felt awful that I hadn't cried sooner. I'm still going through the memories every once in a while. I was peeling apples and making an apple pie and I remembered that last year she told me she would get an apple peeler just for me when I visit her again and I broke down in tears and apple juice in my eyes. I think it's a good think to talk about when people are ready.

snippet.textDisplay:
When my last dog & cat passed away I had to process it in the moment because I had been with them for hours on end when they were both having strokes. (My family had lost 3 pets within the span of 6 months, our dog in the early hours of May 1st, 2017 & our 2 cats on the 4th of July & the one I held closest of the 2 cats only 5 to 15 minutes before it turned midnight of my birthday/November 9th of the same year, I don't know when because I was drawing for the last 15 minutes of that night but I know he had died in the span of 5 to 15 minutes before midnight because I looked back at him 5 minutes before midnight & he was gone.)

It really hurt to see my dog go because he went through that shit for 21 hours with no end & we were only alerted that he was having a stroke when my other dog started barking & crying at my door because she was scared & I was too, I ran downstairs to see him having a seizure, I can't remember if I ran back up the stairs or screamed from downstairs for my dad but I remember crying & my corgi crying for him too.

I was six when I realized there was no santa. My bike said "made in China" and I was like "mom Santa is in the North Pole how come my bike says made in China?"

My mom was like "oh baby Santa has helpers all over the world" but even as a small child I knew. Why do people lie to their children? I do not understand. I would totally rather my mom have said "oh baby you caught me, Santa is a social structure put in place to teach social norms, I'm sorry I tried to smush you into that box baby"...
